or, if you're on the US side of the ocean:

http://www.amazon.com/gp/registry/4HTWP4885GSB/102-7314012-6767349

In any case, have fun with it :)


Installation
============

$ ./configure
$ make
$ make install



Configuration
=============

Edit ModTunnelClient.ini to setup the host to connect to and 
the details of your proxy (if needed), then save it as
~/.ModTunnelClient.ini

You can now launch modtunnelclient, which will fork and stay
in the background.
